<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="155" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[175,380,757,778]" box="[175,380,757,778]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">
<heading box="[175,380,757,778]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="155" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,380,757,778]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[223,311,757,778]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erraticus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[223,311,757,778]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">erraticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[175,1005,797,1137]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">
Members of this group share the following character states: mentum with sides 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1004,797,817]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">6</emphasis>
rounded; tooth narrow and not reaching apices of lobes, paramedian foveal pits indistinct or small; lateral depressions with impressed meshed microsculpture; disc of pronotum with indistinct meshed microsculpture; posterior angles of pronotum right to obtusely rounded, denticulate in some species; elytra without orange spot at apical fourth around suture; elytral microsculpture striate, lines indistinct; epipleuron with subapical plica; metasternum and metepisternum with punctures; metasternum without or with very shallow constriction medially at level of posterior edges of mesocoxae; tarsomeres 5 without setae underneath; endophallus with sclerotized ring; body size medium to large (SBL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[399,417,1036,1056]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">¼</emphasis>
<quantity box="[423,555,1036,1057]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.55" metricValueMax="11.5" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="155" unit="mm" value="9.55" valueMax="11.5" valueMin="7.6">7.6–11.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="155" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[175,1005,797,1137]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">
<materialsCitation collectorName="Ten Nearctic" country="Mexico" location="Pacific" pageId="10" pageNumber="155" specimenCount="1">
<collectorName box="[199,327,1063,1084]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">Ten Nearctic</collectorName>
species are placed in this group. 
<taxonomicName authority="Allen, 1972" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[678,1000,1063,1084]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeariani">
<emphasis box="[678,870,1063,1084]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">Loxandrus yeariani</emphasis>
Allen, 1972
</taxonomicName>
, known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[385,426,1089,1110]" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">type</typeStatus>
locality along the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039387FD5B7B500FFF2CFD76356F5813:8EE560305B7B500FFDDDFBC234AE5A67" box="[606,670,1089,1110]" country="Mexico" name="Pacific" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">Pacific</location>
coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[759,834,1089,1110]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="155">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, possibly belongs to this group (see Allen and Ball 1980:506)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
